Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper discusses a denotational model based on linear logic, and investigates the possibility of a semantic account of execution time for a calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper deals with lambda calculus and its extension, and proposes a measure of execution time. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is relevant because the paper discusses type derivations and their size as a measure of execution time. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is less likely but still possible because the paper uses a machine learning technique called "relational semantics" to model the calculus. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible because the paper proposes a refinement of the syntax and operational semantics of the calculus to get a semantic measure of execution time.
